<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="107" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="107">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="107">
Very similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Microperus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Microperus diversicolor" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diversicolor">Microperus diversicolor</taxonomicName>
(e.g., antennal club type 3), except pronotum bright yellow with brown patch, elytra black, declivity commencing closer to elytral base, declivital interstriae covered with many small sharp hooks (similar as in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Microperus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Microperus parva" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parva">Microperus parva</taxonomicName>
, but larger). Characteristic elytral disc: anterior portion inflated, convex, boundary between elytral disc and declivity slightly concave, impressed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
